{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":873,"text":"1.3 billion years ago,"},{"time":4104,"text":"in a distant, distant galaxy,"},{"time":7198,"text":"two black holes locked into a spiral,"},{"time":10576,"text":"falling inexorably towards each other"},{"time":13234,"text":"and collided,"},{"time":14632,"text":"converting three Suns' worth of stuff"},{"time":17599,"text":"into pure energy in a tenth of a second."},{"time":21769,"text":"For that brief moment in time,"},{"time":24538,"text":"the glow was brighter than all the stars"},{"time":27974,"text":"in all the galaxies"},{"time":29659,"text":"in all of the known Universe."},{"time":32426,"text":"It was a very"},{"time":34226,"text":"big"},{"time":35401,"text":"bang."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38297,"text":"But they didn't release\ntheir energy in light."},{"time":41135,"text":"I mean, you know, they're black holes."},{"time":45229,"text":"All that energy was pumped\ninto the fabric of space and time itself,"},{"time":50094,"text":"making the Universe explode\nin gravitational waves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53731,"text":"Let me give you a sense\nof the timescale at work here."},{"time":57317,"text":"1.3 billion years ago,"},{"time":59952,"text":"Earth had just managed to evolve\nmulticellular life."},{"time":64250,"text":"Since then, Earth has made and evolved"},{"time":67926,"text":"corals, fish, plants, dinosaurs, people\nand even -- God save us -- the Internet."},{"time":74063,"text":"And about 25 years ago,"},{"time":76602,"text":"a particularly audacious set of people --"},{"time":78644,"text":"Rai Weiss at MIT, Kip Thorne\nand Ronald Drever at Caltech --"},{"time":84047,"text":"decided that it would be really neat"},{"time":85865,"text":"to build a giant laser detector"},{"time":88602,"text":"with which to search\nfor the gravitational waves"},{"time":91008,"text":"from things like colliding black holes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94308,"text":"Now, most people thought they were nuts."},{"time":97287,"text":"But enough people realized\nthat they were brilliant nuts"},{"time":101225,"text":"that the US National Science Foundation\ndecided to fund their crazy idea."},{"time":106288,"text":"So after decades of development,"},{"time":109657,"text":"construction and imagination"},{"time":112160,"text":"and a breathtaking amount of hard work,"},{"time":116168,"text":"they built their detector, called LIGO:"},{"time":119343,"text":"The Laser Interferometer\nGravitational-Wave Observatory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124651,"text":"For the last several years,"},{"time":125985,"text":"LIGO's been undergoing\na huge expansion in its accuracy,"},{"time":129608,"text":"a tremendous improvement\nin its detection ability."},{"time":132624,"text":"It's now called Advanced LIGO as a result."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136116,"text":"In early September of 2015,"},{"time":139005,"text":"LIGO turned on for a final test run"},{"time":141885,"text":"while they sorted out\na few lingering details."},{"time":145978,"text":"And on September 14 of 2015,"},{"time":150280,"text":"just days after the detector\nhad gone live,"},{"time":154842,"text":"the gravitational waves\nfrom those colliding black holes"},{"time":158653,"text":"passed through the Earth."},{"time":160977,"text":"And they passed through you and me."},{"time":163590,"text":"And they passed through the detector."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167143,"text":"(Audio) Scott Hughes:\nThere's two moments in my life"},{"time":169668,"text":"more emotionally intense than that."},{"time":171383,"text":"One is the birth of my daughter."},{"time":172946,"text":"The other is when I had to say goodbye\nto my father when he was terminally ill."},{"time":178051,"text":"You know, it was the payoff\nof my career, basically."},{"time":182491,"text":"Everything I'd been working on --\nit's no longer science fiction! (Laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189416,"text":"Allan Adams: So that's my very good friend\nand collaborator, Scott Hughes,"},{"time":193610,"text":"a theoretical physicist at MIT,"},{"time":195825,"text":"who has been studying\ngravitational waves from black holes"},{"time":198634,"text":"and the signals that they could impart\non observatories like LIGO,"},{"time":202187,"text":"for the past 23 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204892,"text":"So let me take a moment to tell you\nwhat I mean by a gravitational wave."},{"time":209489,"text":"A gravitational wave is a ripple"},{"time":212581,"text":"in the shape of space and time."},{"time":215468,"text":"As the wave passes by,"},{"time":217503,"text":"it stretches space and everything in it"},{"time":219906,"text":"in one direction,"},{"time":221089,"text":"and compresses it in the other."},{"time":223893,"text":"This has led to countless instructors\nof general relativity"},{"time":226966,"text":"doing a really silly dance to demonstrate\nin their classes on general relativity."},{"time":230922,"text":"\"It stretches and expands,\nit stretches and expands.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":236080,"text":"So the trouble with gravitational waves"},{"time":238280,"text":"is that they're very weak;\nthey're preposterously weak."},{"time":241302,"text":"For example, the waves that hit us\non September 14 --"},{"time":244724,"text":"and yes, every single one of you\nstretched and compressed"},{"time":249442,"text":"under the action of that wave --"},{"time":251734,"text":"when the waves hit, they stretched\nthe average person"},{"time":254663,"text":"by one part in 10 to the 21."},{"time":257798,"text":"That's a decimal place, 20 zeroes,"},{"time":260694,"text":"and a one."},{"time":263519,"text":"That's why everyone thought\nthe LIGO people were nuts."},{"time":267523,"text":"Even with a laser detector five kilometers\nlong -- and that's already crazy --"},{"time":273429,"text":"they would have to measure\nthe length of those detectors"},{"time":277078,"text":"to less than one thousandth\nof the radius of the nucleus"},{"time":281083,"text":"of an atom."},{"time":282265,"text":"And that's preposterous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284480,"text":"So towards the end\nof his classic text on gravity,"},{"time":288497,"text":"LIGO co-founder Kip Thorne"},{"time":292508,"text":"described the hunt\nfor gravitational waves as follows:"},{"time":295519,"text":"He said, \"The technical difficulties\nto be surmounted"},{"time":298694,"text":"in constructing such detectors"},{"time":301031,"text":"are enormous."},{"time":303574,"text":"But physicists are ingenious,"},{"time":306408,"text":"and with the support\nof a broad lay public,"},{"time":309972,"text":"all obstacles will surely be overcome.\""},{"time":314138,"text":"Thorne published that in 1973,"},{"time":317682,"text":"42 years before he succeeded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323149,"text":"Now, coming back to LIGO,"},{"time":324432,"text":"Scott likes to say that LIGO\nacts like an ear"},{"time":327670,"text":"more than it does like an eye."},{"time":329629,"text":"I want to explain what that means."},{"time":331863,"text":"Visible light has a wavelength, a size,"},{"time":334209,"text":"that's much smaller\nthan the things around you,"},{"time":336806,"text":"the features on people's faces,"},{"time":338329,"text":"the size of your cell phone."},{"time":341582,"text":"And that's really useful,"},{"time":342813,"text":"because it lets you make an image\nor a map of the things around you,"},{"time":346044,"text":"by looking at the light\ncoming from different spots"},{"time":348456,"text":"in the scene about you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349631,"text":"Sound is different."},{"time":352111,"text":"Audible sound has a wavelength\nthat can be up to 50 feet long."},{"time":355585,"text":"And that makes it really difficult --"},{"time":357386,"text":"in fact, in practical purposes,\nimpossible -- to make an image"},{"time":360450,"text":"of something you really care about."},{"time":362292,"text":"Your child's face."},{"time":364777,"text":"Instead, we use sound\nto listen for features like pitch"},{"time":368931,"text":"and tone and rhythm and volume"},{"time":372073,"text":"to infer a story behind the sounds."},{"time":376065,"text":"That's Alice talking."},{"time":377943,"text":"That's Bob interrupting."},{"time":379500,"text":"Silly Bob."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381809,"text":"So, the same is true\nof gravitational waves."},{"time":385688,"text":"We can't use them to make simple images\nof things out in the Universe."},{"time":390776,"text":"But by listening to changes"},{"time":392476,"text":"in the amplitude and frequency\nof those waves,"},{"time":395943,"text":"we can hear the story\nthat those waves are telling."},{"time":400224,"text":"And at least for LIGO,"},{"time":401789,"text":"the frequencies that it can hear\nare in the audio band."},{"time":406011,"text":"So if we convert the wave patterns\ninto pressure waves and air, into sound,"},{"time":411121,"text":"we can literally hear\nthe Universe speaking to us."},{"time":415089,"text":"For example, listening to gravity,\njust in this way,"},{"time":419244,"text":"can tell us a lot about the collision\nof two black holes,"},{"time":421958,"text":"something my colleague Scott has spent\nan awful lot of time thinking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425776,"text":"(Audio) SH: If the two black holes\nare non-spinning,"},{"time":428271,"text":"you get a very simple chirp: whoop!"},{"time":430469,"text":"If the two bodies are spinning\nvery rapidly, I have that same chirp,"},{"time":434146,"text":"but with a modulation on top of it,"},{"time":435892,"text":"so it kind of goes: whir, whir, whir!"},{"time":438281,"text":"It's sort of the vocabulary of spin\nimprinted on this waveform."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443213,"text":"AA: So on September 14, 2015,"},{"time":446524,"text":"a date that's definitely\ngoing to live in my memory,"},{"time":449474,"text":"LIGO heard this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":451743,"text":"[Whirring sound]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454416,"text":"So if you know how to listen,\nthat is the sound of --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":459320,"text":"(Audio) SH: ... two black holes,\neach of about 30 solar masses,"},{"time":462558,"text":"that were whirling around at a rate"},{"time":464274,"text":"comparable to what goes on\nin your blender."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467331,"text":"AA: It's worth pausing here\nto think about what that means."},{"time":470157,"text":"Two black holes, the densest thing\nin the Universe,"},{"time":473466,"text":"one with a mass of 29 Suns"},{"time":475670,"text":"and one with a mass of 36 Suns,"},{"time":478481,"text":"whirling around each other\n100 times per second"},{"time":481178,"text":"before they collide."},{"time":482360,"text":"Just imagine the power of that."},{"time":484819,"text":"It's fantastic."},{"time":487167,"text":"And we know it because we heard it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491827,"text":"That's the lasting importance of LIGO."},{"time":495049,"text":"It's an entirely new way\nto observe the Universe"},{"time":498782,"text":"that we've never had before."},{"time":500663,"text":"It's a way that lets us hear the Universe"},{"time":503751,"text":"and hear the invisible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507496,"text":"And there's a lot out there\nthat we can't see --"},{"time":510556,"text":"in practice or even in principle."},{"time":512208,"text":"So supernova, for example:"},{"time":514241,"text":"I would love to know why very massive\nstars explode in supernovae."},{"time":518709,"text":"They're very useful;"},{"time":519884,"text":"we've learned a lot\nabout the Universe from them."},{"time":522252,"text":"The problem is, all the interesting\nphysics happens in the core,"},{"time":525283,"text":"and the core is hidden behind\nthousands of kilometers"},{"time":527812,"text":"of iron and carbon and silicon."},{"time":529911,"text":"We'll never see through it,\nit's opaque to light."},{"time":532240,"text":"Gravitational waves go through iron\nas if it were glass --"},{"time":536180,"text":"totally transparent."},{"time":538512,"text":"The Big Bang: I would love\nto be able to explore"},{"time":540933,"text":"the first few moments of the Universe,"},{"time":543796,"text":"but we'll never see them,"},{"time":545468,"text":"because the Big Bang itself\nis obscured by its own afterglow."},{"time":550703,"text":"With gravitational waves,"},{"time":552917,"text":"we should be able to see\nall the way back to the beginning."},{"time":556425,"text":"Perhaps most importantly,"},{"time":558243,"text":"I'm positive that there\nare things out there"},{"time":561300,"text":"that we've never seen"},{"time":562915,"text":"that we may never be able to see"},{"time":564692,"text":"and that we haven't even imagined --"},{"time":567969,"text":"things that we'll only\ndiscover by listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571255,"text":"And in fact, even\nin that very first event,"},{"time":573939,"text":"LIGO found things that we didn't expect."},{"time":577564,"text":"Here's my colleague and one of the key\nmembers of the LIGO collaboration,"},{"time":581079,"text":"Matt Evans, my colleague at MIT,\naddressing exactly that:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":584741,"text":"(Audio) Matt Evans: The kinds of stars\nwhich produce the black holes"},{"time":587975,"text":"that we observed here"},{"time":589261,"text":"are the dinosaurs of the Universe."},{"time":591063,"text":"They're these massive things\nthat are old, from prehistoric times,"},{"time":594762,"text":"and the black holes are kind of like\nthe dinosaur bones"},{"time":597432,"text":"with which we do this archeology."},{"time":599074,"text":"So it lets us really get\na whole nother angle"},{"time":601646,"text":"on what's out there in the Universe"},{"time":603551,"text":"and how the stars came to be,\nand in the end, of course,"},{"time":606338,"text":"how we came to be out of this whole mess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610304,"text":"AA: Our challenge now"},{"time":611980,"text":"is to be as audacious as possible."},{"time":615840,"text":"Thanks to LIGO, we know how\nto build exquisite detectors"},{"time":618766,"text":"that can listen to the Universe,"},{"time":620359,"text":"to the rustle and the chirp of the cosmos."},{"time":623890,"text":"Our job is to dream up and build\nnew observatories --"},{"time":627102,"text":"a whole new generation of observatories --"},{"time":629157,"text":"on the ground, in space."},{"time":631559,"text":"I mean, what could be more glorious\nthan listening to the Big Bang itself?"},{"time":636973,"text":"Our job now is to dream big."},{"time":639552,"text":"Dream with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640807,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641990,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}